|YK0s                                                                        s|XX0
|YK0s  |WK0Syntax: |YKBndoom <parvus|mediocris|amplus>       |WK0Cost: |YKBVaries            s|XX0
|YK0s                                                                        s|XX0
|YK0s    The doom curse is one of the most dangerous spells available to a   s|XX0
|YK0s   Necromancer. The Necromancer pulls together their blight magic into  s|XX0
|YK0s   a powerful mist that will choke the life from all of the enemies in  s|XX0
|YK0s  the area. The damage is split among all valid targets. A Necromancer  s|XX0
|YK0s  can choose one of three modes for the doom spell, which will default  s|XX0
|YK0s     to using 'parvus'. The 'parvus' mode is the weakest, which will    s|XX0
|YK0s   cause a small amount of damage, but only have a short cooldown and   s|XX0
|YK0s      small cost. The 'mediocris' mode costs more and has a longer      s|XX0
|YK0s  cooldown, but does more damage. The strongest mode, 'amplus', does a  s|XX0
|YK0s            large amount of damage but has the highest costs.           s|XX0
|YK0s                                                                        s|XX0
|YK0s     The 'parvus' setting requires 25% of maximum sp to cast. The       s|XX0
|YK0s  'mediocris' and 'amplus' settings require 50%, and 75% of maximum     s|XX0
|YK0s                     sp to cast, respectively.                          s|XX0
|YK0s                                                                        s|XX0
